# gen142 (E7) STRESS — ~10x the toy case: three overlapping named worlds, the
# SAME entities (rex, max) meaning different things in each, scope switching,
# "what is assumed?", an anonymous-then-named scratch world, explicit teardown
# AND leave, and a final proof that NOTHING leaked into permanent memory.

# Build two worlds that disagree about the same names.
> in the saga world rex is a dragon
< In the saga world, rex is a dragon.
> in the saga world max is a knight
< In the saga world, max is a knight.
> is rex a dragon?
< Yes.
> in the office world rex is a manager
< In the office world, rex is a manager.
> in the office world max is an intern
< In the office world, max is an intern.

# The office scope is active now, so the same name answers differently.
> who is rex?
< In the office world, rex is a manager.

# Switch back to the saga scope and read its overlay.
> in the saga world
< Opened the saga world. Tell me what is true in it.
> who is max?
< In the saga world, max is a knight.
> what is assumed?
< In the saga world I am assuming: rex is a dragon; max is a knight.

# A class true in office but never assumed in saga is unknown here, not false.
> is max a manager?
< Not assumed in the saga world.

# A third, named world started explicitly; its rex is a third thing.
> start a world called dream
< Opened the dream world. Tell me what is true in it.
> rex is a cloud
< In the dream world, rex is a cloud.
> who is rex?
< In the dream world, rex is a cloud.

# Switch to office; its rex is unchanged by the dream scope.
> in the office world
< Opened the office world. Tell me what is true in it.
> who is rex?
< In the office world, rex is a manager.

# Tear the dream world down, leave the active scope.
> forget the dream world
< Forgotten the dream world; none of it reached my memory.
> leave the world
< Left the office world.

# No world is active: a fact now reaches permanent memory and answers normally.
> bob is a human
< Learned: human(bob).
> is bob a human?
< Yes.

# Anti-leak: none of the three worlds' facts ever entered permanent memory.
> is rex a dragon?
< I don't know about dragon.
